Package io.shiromi.saml.types

Class BooleanType

java.lang.Object
io.shiromi.saml.types.AbstractType<Boolean>
io.shiromi.saml.types.BooleanType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public final class BooleanType extends AbstractType<Boolean>
Instances of the class BooleanType have a boolean as value, therefore it carries the same functionality as boolean does, however, the operations are in written form, e.g. AND is equal to && other, it also carries functionality for parsing from different types, such as String. The main implementation of this class is for logical operations, like and, all of which are supported by this class.

The logical operators supported by this class are:
Operation Method Short description
∧andtrue if both are true
∧...∧and...andtrue if all are true
∨ortrue if either is true
∨...∨or...ortrue if any is true
⊕xortrue if one is true
⊕...⊕xor...xortrue if an odd number is true
¬∧nandfalse if both are true
¬(∧...∧)nand...nandfalse if all are true
¬∨norfalse if either is true
¬(∨...∨)nor...norfalse if any is true
¬⊕xnorfalse if one is true
¬(⊕...⊕)xnor...xnorfalse if an odd number is true
¬nottrue if false and vice-versa
Version:
1.0
Author:
Shiromi
